Food and Feeding.
Feeding habits of Galapagos Sea Lions are not well studied, but they eat sardines (
Clupeidae
), lanternfish (
Myctophidae
), deep-sea smelts (
Bathylagidae
), and squid. During El Nino weather patterns when food resources are scarce, greeneye fish (Chlorophtalmidae) are added to the diet. Galapagos Sea Lions will thrash octopuses at the water’s surface, presumably before eating them. Lactating females feed both day and night, in contrast to nocturnally feeding Galapagos Fur Seals (
Arctocephalus galapagoensus
).
